  "content": "line-height: 1.7;\">\n      I use corvia (the project I'm building) to persist all research. Claude queries the knowledge base at the start of every session. Prior decisions, rejected alternatives, and design rationale are all searchable.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"insight-box\">\n    <p style=\"font-size: 18px;\">When I revisited the retrieval pipeline three weeks after the initial design, corvia surfaced what I'd already explored and what had changed. The exploration picked up where it left off instead of starting from scratch.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">06 / 09</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- SLIDE 7: LAYER 2 - DEV LOOP -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\" style=\"color: var(--accent-green);\">Layer 2: Autonomous Execution</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"font-size: 54px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\n    Issue In.<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-green\">Merged PR Out.</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">\n    I type <span style=\"font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; background: #0d1117; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 18px; color: var(--accent-green);\">/dev-loop 14</span> and it runs autonomously. The dev-loop is a skill file that Claude Code reads. It orchestrates the full pipeline.\n  </div>",
